1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,880
 "Whew, what a weekend we've had and incredible."

2
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:09,520
 I feel like my friend who, whenever he's done eating a meal, he pushes back from the table

3
00:00:09,520 --> 00:00:13,520
 and he goes, "Is it supposed to hurt when you're done eating?"

4
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:14,520
 Right?

5
00:00:14,520 --> 00:00:18,360
 Like, I feel like that kind of weekend where it's just like, "Could there be more?"

6
00:00:18,360 --> 00:00:22,120
 And then the answer, of course, is yes, there's more.

7
00:00:22,120 --> 00:00:24,000
 There's more.

8
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:28,060
 And our task here is to increase our capacity, right?

9
00:00:28,060 --> 00:00:32,800
 It's not that there's more of God, it's that there's more room in us for the God who fills

10
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,940
 us in every way.

11
00:00:34,940 --> 00:00:41,260
 And I still remember the day that my eldest son went to first day of school, kindergarten.

12
00:00:41,260 --> 00:00:43,900
 And I was living in Australia at the time.

13
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:48,340
 And so he was about five and he wanted to walk by himself even, you know, like I couldn't

14
00:00:48,340 --> 00:00:49,340
 hold his hand.

15
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:51,980
 He was like all independent, went to school first day.

16
00:00:51,980 --> 00:00:52,980
 And it was quite a day.

17
00:00:52,980 --> 00:00:54,540
 And then when he got home, I was all excited.

18
00:00:54,540 --> 00:00:56,700
 And I said to him, you know, "How did it go?

19
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:58,740
 You know, your first day of kindergarten in Australia.

20
00:00:58,740 --> 00:01:01,500
 I mean, like, come on, how was it?"

21
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:02,500
 And he said, "It was boring."

22
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:07,340
 I was like, "How could it be boring?"

23
00:01:07,340 --> 00:01:11,500
 And he said, "Well, all we did today was we just literally took turns telling stories

24
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:15,260
 about what we had done over the summer break."

25
00:01:15,260 --> 00:01:17,580
 And I said, "That doesn't sound boring.

26
00:01:17,580 --> 00:01:19,940
 Like we did some actual cool things over the summer break."

27
00:01:19,940 --> 00:01:21,940
 I was like, "So what did you share?

28
00:01:21,940 --> 00:01:23,580
 Like, what was your story?"

29
00:01:23,580 --> 00:01:31,820
 And he said, "Well, I wanted mine to be really good so I made one up."

30
00:01:31,820 --> 00:01:32,820
 And I said, "Really?"

31
00:01:32,820 --> 00:01:36,100
 I had a spot of preacher's kid.

32
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:37,820
 So I said, "Well, what did you say?"

33
00:01:37,820 --> 00:01:43,740
 And he goes, "Well, mom, you remember that time back in Canada when I was in that go-kart

34
00:01:43,740 --> 00:01:49,060
 race and I was going around the track and then all of a sudden my go-kart, it like exploded

35
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:51,340
 and it turned into a motorcycle.

36
00:01:51,340 --> 00:01:55,180
 And then I ran that motorcycle all the way through and I won and they gave me that big

37
00:01:55,180 --> 00:01:56,180
 gold trophy."

38
00:01:56,180 --> 00:01:59,820
 And I said, "Nope.

39
00:01:59,820 --> 00:02:00,820
 Don't remember."

40
00:02:00,820 --> 00:02:05,000
 And then he just looked at me and he put his hand on my head like this and he just closed

41
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,000
 his eyes.

42
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:13,620
 And then he said, "Do you remember now?"

43
00:02:13,620 --> 00:02:20,600
 My son, his name is Zion, what he's after is a better story.

44
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,620
 He's after a better story.

45
00:02:22,620 --> 00:02:24,100
 It's what we're all after.

46
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:28,700
 Actually, sometimes I think when we get to heaven, the first day of heaven is just going

47
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:32,980
 to be us telling stories about what we did on our summer break and I want mine to be

48
00:02:32,980 --> 00:02:35,500
 a good one.

49
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:40,340
 And here's the thing, I think the way that Jesus invites us to live our lives is we don't

50
00:02:40,340 --> 00:02:42,460
 have to make it up.

51
00:02:42,460 --> 00:02:44,660
 Our stories will be good.

52
00:02:44,660 --> 00:02:45,780
 Our stories will be worthy.

53
00:02:45,780 --> 00:02:52,520
 Our stories will be helpful and good and full of the abundant Zoe life that Jesus offers

54
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:55,880
 us if we'll live that way.

55
00:02:55,880 --> 00:03:00,960
 And in some ways, even coming to church together like this and worshiping and remembering,

56
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:05,040
 I mean, even that last song of worship is from a guy who was a prisoner on an island

57
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:07,120
 of Patmos like under the boot of the empire.

58
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:12,480
 I mean, literally, like Christians are being persecuted everywhere in Rome and he's mustering

59
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:13,480
 up.

60
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:14,480
 I mean, I can only...

61
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:15,480
 It was not anything like that.

62
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:18,200
 He's like a little girl in the middle of nowhere and he's probably just going like, "I sing

63
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:19,200
 holy."

64
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:24,280
 Like he's trying to muster up his own sense of self and he says, "I'm worshiping on the

65
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:26,200
 Lord's day as a prisoner."

66
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:32,040
 And then all of a sudden, I hear this voice from heaven like a trumpet and it says, "Come

67
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:33,040
 on up here.

68
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:34,040
 Come up here.

69
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:36,280
 I want to show you some things.

70
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:38,280
 I want to tell you some things.

71
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:42,200
 I want to tell you some things that are more real than the real you're experiencing right

72
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:47,320
 now that are more true, that they're the character of God, the invitation that God has for all

73
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:50,280
 of his children to be beloved, to be known.

74
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,640
 You know, come up here.

75
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,000
 Come up now."

76
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:56,360
 And all the angels cry, "Holy."

77
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:58,840
 And this is sort of this resetting, this invitation.

78
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:03,640
 I want to take a look at the life of the disciples in Mark chapter four, just really quick, just

79
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:08,360
 like a little story that's kind of set in the life of Jesus and the disciples.

80
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:13,320
 There's this one more, you know, in this rhythm that Jesus has where he's always inviting

81
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:16,120
 people to come, come and see.

82
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:21,200
 And this is one of the great problems that we have sometimes in our faith journey and

83
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:27,720
 Christianity is somehow we've come under this idea that is an illusion that Christianity

84
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:30,520
 is about what we believe.

85
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,520
 You know, there's just a construct.

86
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:33,160
 There's just another religion.

87
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:34,760
 There's just a construct of belief.

88
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:38,680
 And so we say like, "If we believe these things or if I hold to these things, then that's

89
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:39,680
 what this is."

90
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:41,600
 It's just like a practice of another religion.

91
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:43,400
 But it's not.

92
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:44,400
 It's not.

93
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:45,400
 That's an illusion.

94
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:51,600
 The real thing, like the real faith practice is an invitation to actually follow Jesus.

95
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:55,600
 It's an invitation to come, to see, to taste, to move.

96
00:04:55,600 --> 00:05:02,920
 The invitation to follow Jesus is always a disruption to status quo and an invitation

97
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:08,760
 into growth and a reality to experience something that is beyond what we could even ever conjure

98
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:10,840
 up in our best stories.

99
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:11,840
 And so this is one of those.

100
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:15,840
 This is like a little tiny snapshot in the life of Jesus and the disciples that I think

101
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:21,720
 holds some keys to this disruptive reimagining of what our faith is and what it means to

102
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:22,720
 follow Jesus.

103
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:26,520
 And it's in Mark's Gospel, chapter 4, near the end.

104
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:27,520
 We're all going to read it together.

105
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:30,080
 I'm just going to invite you to read it out loud with me.

106
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,480
 Are you ready?

107
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,480
 Here we go.

108
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:35,520
 Mark 4, starting at verse 35, and let's go.

109
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:42,280
 That day, when evening came, he said to his disciples, "Let us go over to the other side."

110
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:47,720
 And leaving the crowd behind, they took him along just as he was in the boat.

111
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,960
 There were also other boats with him.

112
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:56,440
 A furious squall came up, and the waves broke over the boat so that it was nearly swamped.

113
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:59,820
 Jesus was in the stern, sleeping on a cushion.

114
00:05:59,820 --> 00:06:05,640
 And the disciples woke him and said to him, "Teacher, don't you care if we drown?"

115
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:11,480
 He got up, rebuked the wind, and said to the waves, "Quiet, be still."

116
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:15,160
 Then the wind died down, and it was completely calm.

117
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:18,760
 He said to his disciples, "Why are you so afraid?

118
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:20,840
 Do you still have no faith?"

119
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:25,020
 They were terrified and asked each other, "Who is this?"

120
00:06:25,020 --> 00:06:28,600
 Even the wind and the waves obeyed him.

121
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,800
 Amen.

122
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:35,120
 This invitation that Jesus gives to the disciples in this context is a disruption.

123
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:41,080
 And it's a disruption because, number one, they're killing it.

124
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:44,120
 They're doing amazing.

125
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:47,560
 If you read a little bit before this, you'll see they're in the...

126
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:48,720
 Jesus is just killing it in mystery.

127
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:50,200
 He's just like, he's winning.

128
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,280
 There's crowds of people.

129
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:52,400
 He's healing everybody.

130
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:56,440
 People are being healed of diseases and cured of evil spirits, and they're just like, whispers

131
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:57,440
 are going everywhere.

132
00:06:57,440 --> 00:06:59,400
 This is probably the one who was expected.

133
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:00,640
 This is probably the Messiah.

134
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:01,640
 There's all these...

135
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:03,860
 I mean, the disciples are probably just living their best lives.

136
00:07:03,860 --> 00:07:07,160
 Their moms are just like, "That's my boy over there with that rabbi who's healing all the

137
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,160
 people."

138
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,160
 I mean, it's just like, "Woo-hoo!"

139
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:12,040
 And Jesus is like, "Yeah, we should...

140
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:13,040
 Now's a good time to go."

141
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:16,360
 It's like, "No, now's not a good time to go.

142
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:20,080
 Now's a good time to stay, because if we stay here, we could keep building this thing.

143
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,960
 We could be the height of success.

144
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:23,640
 We could be like, the dreams could come true.

145
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:25,560
 My mom could be actually proud of me."

146
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:27,280
 And then Jesus is like, "No, let's go."

147
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:31,040
 And when he says, "Let's go to the other side," it's not just like, "Let's go to the other

148
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:34,800
 side of the lake, because it's better over there."

149
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:38,520
 It's like, "Let's go to the other side of the tracks."

150
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:42,960
 It's like, "Let's go to that part of the lake where your mom said, 'Don't go there.'"

151
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:45,080
 Because over there are all the compromisers.

152
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:48,440
 Over there are all the pig farmers, which if you're Jewish and kosher at all, you know

153
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:49,880
 that's not what you want to be near.

154
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:55,320
 Over there is where all those Roman sympathizers are, all those sellouts of the empire.

155
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:58,280
 Over there is where all of those people live.

156
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:59,280
 Don't go over there.

157
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:03,640
 And in the midst of this successful, amazing ministry, Jesus says, "Yeah, we should...

158
00:08:03,640 --> 00:08:05,920
 You know where we should go?"

159
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:13,080
 I remember living in Australia, and I was doing some social justice work there, trying

160
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:18,200
 to help women who were suffering from sexual exploitation within a brothel system that

161
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:19,200
 was legalized.

162
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,200
 So it's really tricky.

163
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,280
 And I just remember going, "I don't even know how to do this.

164
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:23,280
 This is crazy."

165
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:25,360
 And I was asking the Lord, "How are we going to do this?"

166
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:29,040
 And I got this call from this friend's mother.

167
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:33,280
 She's a retired Baptist lady in a suburb in Australia.

168
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:36,480
 And she says, "Danielle, I need to meet with you."

169
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:39,840
 So you always say yes to your friend's mom, right?

170
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:42,320
 So I met with her, and she said, "I was...

171
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:48,440
 Oh," she said, "I keep getting these calls because my number, my phone number is only

172
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:53,120
 one digit different from the local brothel in my neighborhood's phone number."

173
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:57,000
 So she said, "I keep getting these calls, you know, and they're really disruptive.

174
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,000
 I don't want these calls."

175
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:01,640
 So she said, "I decided that I would change my phone number."

176
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:05,640
 So she said, "On the day that I was going to go change my phone number, I was doing

177
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:10,600
 my devotions in the morning like a good Baptist should, and she said the Holy Spirit spoke

178
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:11,600
 to me."

179
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,600
 I said, "Awkward."

180
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:19,800
 Anyway, and she said, "The Holy Spirit said, 'Jan, why are you changing your phone number?'"

181
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:23,800
 And she said, "Well, because the local brothel, you know, but I keep getting these calls."

182
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:31,640
 And she said, "I felt like the Holy Spirit said to me, 'I know I'm sending them.'"

183
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:34,040
 And she said to me, "So what should I do?"

184
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:38,800
 And I'm thinking to myself, "I don't know.

185
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:39,800
 What?

186
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:42,640
 Am I an expert on grandma mobilization?"

187
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:43,640
 You know, like I...

188
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:48,160
 You know, but then I'm also like hearing the Holy Spirit say like, "Hey," right?

189
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:51,400
 So when you don't know what to do, you just ask more questions, right?

190
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:53,520
 Like as a leader, you're not allowed to go like, "I don't know.

191
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:54,520
 This is crazy.

192
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:55,520
 I don't know what I'm doing."

193
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:58,720
 As a leader, you have to go, "Oh, interesting question you have there, Jan.

194
00:09:58,720 --> 00:09:59,720
 Hmm, I don't want.

195
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,720
 I wonder."

196
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:05,640
 You know, so I said, "What would you normally do if you had a neighbor?

197
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:06,880
 You know, you're a neighborly person.

198
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:07,880
 You're a Christian in your community.

199
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:09,920
 Like, what would you do if someone had an accident?

200
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:12,960
 You know, your neighbor moved in and was new from another country.

201
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,520
 Like, what would you normally do?

202
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:16,920
 What would be your normal response as a good neighbor?"

203
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:17,920
 She said, "Oh, that's easy.

204
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:21,120
 I would just bake some cupcakes and go visit."

205
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,440
 And I'm like, "Great.

206
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,440
 Let's do that."

207
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:24,440
 She said, "Do what?"

208
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:27,160
 I'm like, "Well, you're going to have to bake.

209
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:28,160
 I don't do that.

210
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:33,160
 But like you bake the cupcakes and we'll go visit your local brothel."

211
00:10:33,160 --> 00:10:37,520
 And she's like, "That's the strategy?"

212
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:39,080
 I'm like, "Yes, Padawan."

213
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:40,080
 I'm like, "I..."

214
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:43,440
 And the whole weekend, she's like baking, baking, baking, praying, praying, praying.

215
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:46,400
 And the whole weekend, I'm praying, "God, please don't kill Jan.

216
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:47,960
 Like, please don't let her die.

217
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:50,080
 Like, please let this be a good strategy.

218
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,480
 Like, ah, what have I done?

219
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:52,920
 You know, it's my friend's mom.

220
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:54,880
 Like, I'm just like, ah."

221
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:58,080
 And anyway, we meet together at the headquarters where I worked.

222
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,800
 And it's just a couple blocks away, this brothel.

223
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,120
 And we meet together to pray.

224
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:02,120
 And she's got the cupcakes.

225
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,400
 And I'm like ready to go.

226
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,400
 And we're praying up a storm.

227
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:07,360
 And she says to me, you know, "This weekend when I was praying, I felt like God said to

228
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:09,240
 me, 'Jan, this...

229
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:10,240
 Like this is good.

230
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,320
 But like I want you to do this by myself.

231
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:13,320
 Like by yourself.

232
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:15,540
 Like you do it.'"

233
00:11:15,540 --> 00:11:18,080
 And I remember saying to her, "But like, but I'm like the expert."

234
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:19,080
 Right?

235
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:21,440
 Like, I'm like the social...

236
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:23,200
 I've got like a title and everything.

237
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:24,200
 Like I'm ready.

238
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:26,840
 Like I'm headquarters material.

239
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:27,840
 You know, like I'm mobile.

240
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:29,400
 Like I'm the...

241
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:32,480
 And she said, "Yeah, you're the expert, but I'm the neighbor."

