00:23:10,940 --> 00:23:11,940
 It's my wheelchair, man.

492
00:23:11,940 --> 00:23:12,940
 It's my stretcher.

493
00:23:12,940 --> 00:23:16,060
 I've only got Jesus."

494
00:23:16,060 --> 00:23:19,760
 And Jesus got me when I needed Jesus most.

495
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:24,100
 When I was raging against the world and the world was raging against me and I said, "Do

496
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:25,100
 I even matter?

497
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:26,380
 And is God even real?

498
00:23:26,380 --> 00:23:28,820
 And does he even care?"

499
00:23:28,820 --> 00:23:34,460
 And I encountered a God who indeed was real and did care.

500
00:23:34,460 --> 00:23:37,260
 And I remember she sent an email right that night.

501
00:23:37,260 --> 00:23:38,780
 She said, "I didn't mean to call you weak.

502
00:23:38,780 --> 00:23:39,980
 I wasn't trying to insult you.

503
00:23:39,980 --> 00:23:40,980
 I don't mean..."

504
00:23:40,980 --> 00:23:42,540
 I said, "No, you nailed it.

505
00:23:42,540 --> 00:23:43,540
 You got it.

506
00:23:43,540 --> 00:23:44,540
 Sleep tight.

507
00:23:44,540 --> 00:23:45,540
 Don't worry."

508
00:23:45,540 --> 00:23:51,020
 I don't mean I'm not weak on the basketball court, but in general, I'm...

509
00:23:51,020 --> 00:23:52,580
 And back and forth, this flurry of games.

510
00:23:52,580 --> 00:23:54,420
 Finally, she said, "Look, could we meet for coffee?"

511
00:23:54,420 --> 00:23:56,740
 And she had been raised by high-power lawyers.

512
00:23:56,740 --> 00:23:59,240
 She's mayor of the city council.

513
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:01,860
 She's running a whole program at the school.

514
00:24:01,860 --> 00:24:06,620
 She's just like, all she knows is strength and projection and champion and victory.

515
00:24:06,620 --> 00:24:10,820
 And she meets me for coffee in this coffee shop, and she goes to say hi, but instead,

516
00:24:10,820 --> 00:24:11,820
 she just starts weeping.

517
00:24:11,820 --> 00:24:12,820
 She says, "I'm so weak.

518
00:24:12,820 --> 00:24:13,820
 I'm so weak."

519
00:24:13,820 --> 00:24:19,180
 I'm like, "Oh, thank God.

520
00:24:19,180 --> 00:24:22,300
 Can we just get to the end of ourselves?

521
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:26,660
 Can we just get to the end of ourselves and the start of God?

522
00:24:26,660 --> 00:24:27,660
 I'm so weak.

523
00:24:27,660 --> 00:24:28,660
 Does God even care?

524
00:24:28,660 --> 00:24:29,820
 Is this even real?

525
00:24:29,820 --> 00:24:35,340
 Could we just be real and honest?"

526
00:24:35,340 --> 00:24:36,460
 You know, it's really interesting.

527
00:24:36,460 --> 00:24:37,460
 I love...

528
00:24:37,460 --> 00:24:42,020
 Part of the thing I love about the story is that Jesus does not rebuke their question.

529
00:24:42,020 --> 00:24:44,540
 He responds.

530
00:24:44,540 --> 00:24:46,260
 He doesn't respond with words.

531
00:24:46,260 --> 00:24:49,220
 He responds with presence, with action.

532
00:24:49,220 --> 00:24:52,180
 He responds to their need, their deepest concern.

533
00:24:52,180 --> 00:24:54,340
 Do you even care if we drown?

534
00:24:54,340 --> 00:24:59,820
 Jesus is like, "Watch this," and responds.

535
00:24:59,820 --> 00:25:01,340
 "Quiet.

536
00:25:01,340 --> 00:25:06,340
 Be still," he says to the sea.

537
00:25:06,340 --> 00:25:07,340
 "Quiet.

538
00:25:07,340 --> 00:25:08,340
 Be still."

539
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:09,340
 Jesus cares.

540
00:25:09,340 --> 00:25:16,420
 That's the answer to their question, not in a theological textbook, not in a teaching

541
00:25:16,420 --> 00:25:22,740
 time, in the middle of the storms of the boat, where David even says, "I finally figured

542
00:25:22,740 --> 00:25:28,500
 out if I get to the top of the glorious heavens, there God is, and if I make my bed in the

543
00:25:28,500 --> 00:25:33,780
 depths of hell, there God is."

544
00:25:33,780 --> 00:25:37,340
 Does he care?

545
00:25:37,340 --> 00:25:39,580
 He responds.

546
00:25:39,580 --> 00:25:43,380
 And Jesus answers with two questions.

547
00:25:43,380 --> 00:25:49,540
 Do you know that Jesus asked over 323 questions in the Gospels, if you add them all up?

548
00:25:49,540 --> 00:25:55,420
 He was asked 189, and he only answered directly three.

549
00:25:55,420 --> 00:26:00,580
 I was so convicted as a Christian leader, you know, where you come to this place, and

550
00:26:00,580 --> 00:26:08,220
 all we do is give people answers, and all Jesus did was give people questions.

551
00:26:08,220 --> 00:26:14,420
 And the two questions that he says are this, "Why are you so afraid?"

552
00:26:14,420 --> 00:26:21,460
 Now I used to read the questions of Jesus like sarcastic rebuttals, you know, like,

553
00:26:21,460 --> 00:26:24,900
 "Why are you so afraid?

554
00:26:24,900 --> 00:26:27,340
 Where's your faith?"

555
00:26:27,340 --> 00:26:32,580
 And then I progressed to Jesus more like passive-aggressive, like my mom, like, "Are you going to wear

556
00:26:32,580 --> 00:26:33,580
 that?"

557
00:26:33,580 --> 00:26:34,580
 Right?

558
00:26:34,580 --> 00:26:35,580
 Passive-aggressive.

559
00:26:35,580 --> 00:26:42,780
 We're asking questions, but really we're just trying to say the thing, you know?

560
00:26:42,780 --> 00:26:44,260
 And then I actually thought, "You know what?

561
00:26:44,260 --> 00:26:54,100
 I think I might just actually assume that Jesus is really asking genuine questions.

562
00:26:54,100 --> 00:26:57,220
 What if Jesus is really wanting to know?

563
00:26:57,220 --> 00:26:58,940
 What if they're like legitimate questions?"

564
00:26:58,940 --> 00:27:00,180
 But this is a really great...

565
00:27:00,180 --> 00:27:05,860
 I spent years just printing off all the questions of Jesus and asking them.

566
00:27:05,860 --> 00:27:06,860
 They're amazing.

567
00:27:06,860 --> 00:27:10,220
 Like questions like, "Do you want to be well?"

568
00:27:10,220 --> 00:27:15,780
 I just spent a week of my life letting Jesus ask me, "Do you want to be well?

569
00:27:15,780 --> 00:27:17,660
 Do you want to be well?"

570
00:27:17,660 --> 00:27:20,340
 These questions, "Why are you so afraid?"

571
00:27:20,340 --> 00:27:26,580
 I think he genuinely wants to know, "Why are you so afraid?"

572
00:27:26,580 --> 00:27:29,220
 Fear is the currency of oppression.

573
00:27:29,220 --> 00:27:30,220
 Fear is...

574
00:27:30,220 --> 00:27:31,620
 It's a currency, so you get caught up.

575
00:27:31,620 --> 00:27:35,940
 So if fear is motivating you, whatever your decision is, you will either be oppressed

576
00:27:35,940 --> 00:27:38,700
 or you'll be oppressing somebody else.

577
00:27:38,700 --> 00:27:41,740
 If fear is your motivator, it will get you into a currency.

578
00:27:41,740 --> 00:27:42,940
 That's how oppression works.

579
00:27:42,940 --> 00:27:45,740
 It's currency is fear.

580
00:27:45,740 --> 00:27:48,060
 And we live in a currency of fear.

581
00:27:48,060 --> 00:27:51,980
 I mean, all around the world, we've never been so afraid.

582
00:27:51,980 --> 00:27:56,460
 And I feel like part of the formation, the resistance, when Jesus invites us to go with

583
00:27:56,460 --> 00:27:59,980
 him, which is what discipleship is, to cross over to the other side, to respond to the

584
00:27:59,980 --> 00:28:07,220
 cry of the world, one of the questions he asks us is, "Why are we so afraid?"

585
00:28:07,220 --> 00:28:12,860
 And it's a good question because you can't deal with fear if you're not willing to name

586
00:28:12,860 --> 00:28:15,540
 the fear, right?

587
00:28:15,540 --> 00:28:18,940
 You can't deal with fear by denying fear.

588
00:28:18,940 --> 00:28:22,020
 You can't deal with fear by like putting up the, "I am not afraid.

589
00:28:22,020 --> 00:28:25,980
 I am not afraid," and saying it 10 times a day so that finally you're not afraid.

590
00:28:25,980 --> 00:28:31,940
 You've got to deal with fear by actually naming the fear and then inviting a power greater

591
00:28:31,940 --> 00:28:34,620
 than the fear, which the scripture is very clear.

592
00:28:34,620 --> 00:28:39,020
 The power greater than the fear is perfect love, and perfect love is the person of Jesus.

593
00:28:39,020 --> 00:28:43,940
 And Jesus is with them, and he says, "Why are you so afraid?"

594
00:28:43,940 --> 00:28:46,700
 And when you really get honest with this, I mean, why are you so afraid?

595
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:49,300
 I mean, what are you afraid of?

596
00:28:49,300 --> 00:28:52,780
 When Jesus is inviting you to cross over, when Jesus is disrupting your life, what are

597
00:28:52,780 --> 00:28:53,780
 we afraid of?

598
00:28:53,780 --> 00:28:55,300
 We're afraid of looking like fools.

599
00:28:55,300 --> 00:28:56,740
 We're afraid of losing favor maybe.

600
00:28:56,740 --> 00:28:57,740
 I'm afraid of failing.

601
00:28:57,740 --> 00:28:58,740
 I'm terrified of failing.

602
00:28:58,740 --> 00:28:59,740
 Maybe I'll say the wrong thing.

603
00:28:59,740 --> 00:29:00,740
 Maybe I'll say the right thing.

604
00:29:00,740 --> 00:29:01,740
 I don't know.

605
00:29:01,740 --> 00:29:02,740
 Maybe people will love me.

606
00:29:02,740 --> 00:29:03,740
 Maybe people will hate me.

607
00:29:03,740 --> 00:29:09,020
 I mean, the fears are endless, but getting honest with the fear, why are you so afraid?

608
00:29:09,020 --> 00:29:15,700
 And then realizing, "Ah, in the middle of my fear, here is one who is perfect love,

609
00:29:15,700 --> 00:29:20,100
 who can drive it out, who can drive it out."

610
00:29:20,100 --> 00:29:23,260
 And the second question, in the NIV, it puts it in a weird way.

611
00:29:23,260 --> 00:29:26,820
 It says, the one that we just read, it says, "Have you no faith?"

612
00:29:26,820 --> 00:29:31,140
 The question really in the text is, "Where is your faith?"

613
00:29:31,140 --> 00:29:32,380
 They obviously have faith.

614
00:29:32,380 --> 00:29:33,540
 They're in the boat with Jesus.

615
00:29:33,540 --> 00:29:34,740
 They're going to the other side.

616
00:29:34,740 --> 00:29:35,740
 Three cheers for the disciples.

617
00:29:35,740 --> 00:29:36,740
 They did it.

618
00:29:36,740 --> 00:29:37,740
 You know, they're doing it.

619
00:29:37,740 --> 00:29:38,740
 They're on the journey.

620
00:29:38,740 --> 00:29:44,600
 And again, just for the record, the journey is the point.

621
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:46,260
 To be like Jesus is the point.

622
00:29:46,260 --> 00:29:49,380
 We're always constantly, "Once I get to the other side, that'll be the point."

623
00:29:49,380 --> 00:29:52,460
 No, the point is to encounter Jesus.

624
00:29:52,460 --> 00:29:56,900
 To be with Jesus, to be honest with Jesus, to ask the questions of Jesus, to have an

625
00:29:56,900 --> 00:29:57,980
 encounter with Jesus.

626
00:29:57,980 --> 00:29:58,980
 That is the point.

627
00:29:58,980 --> 00:30:02,420
 They're living the point.

628
00:30:02,420 --> 00:30:06,060
 And he says, "Where is your faith?"

629
00:30:06,060 --> 00:30:07,060
 I love it.

630
00:30:07,060 --> 00:30:10,060
 "Where is your faith?"

631
00:30:10,060 --> 00:30:13,820
 I would imagine, I mean, I'm just making this up, but I'd imagine some of their faith might

632
00:30:13,820 --> 00:30:15,820
 have been in their own ability.

633
00:30:15,820 --> 00:30:18,100
 They're sailors.

634
00:30:18,100 --> 00:30:20,580
 They've crossed that sea a bunch of times.

635
00:30:20,580 --> 00:30:24,060
 I mean, part of their faith might have been in their own ability, and they're getting

636
00:30:24,060 --> 00:30:27,020
 to the end of that in a real quick hurry.

637
00:30:27,020 --> 00:30:29,500
 Which by the way, the end of yourself is the beginning of God.

638
00:30:29,500 --> 00:30:31,340
 It's a beautiful place to get to.

639
00:30:31,340 --> 00:30:35,020
 The sweet surrender of getting to the end of your own capacity where you realize the

640
00:30:35,020 --> 00:30:40,180
 faith that you had in these things, even your own things, are not going to get you there.

641
00:30:40,180 --> 00:30:45,900
 You're going to need to put your faith in something real.

642
00:30:45,900 --> 00:30:48,940
 Where is your faith?

643
00:30:48,940 --> 00:30:52,300
 You know, it's not about quantity faith, right?

644
00:30:52,300 --> 00:30:53,300
 Jesus told us this.

645
00:30:53,300 --> 00:30:54,300
 It's just like a mustard seed.

646
00:30:54,300 --> 00:30:56,500
 You just need a tiny little bit.

647
00:30:56,500 --> 00:31:03,820
 But locating it and putting that faith in the one who is faithful, that's a work.

648
00:31:03,820 --> 00:31:04,820
 That's a work.

649
00:31:04,820 --> 00:31:06,020
 That's a work of discipleship.

650
00:31:06,020 --> 00:31:07,020
 Locating your faith.

651
00:31:07,020 --> 00:31:08,020
 Where is your faith?

652
00:31:08,020 --> 00:31:10,140
 Is your faith in a political system or an outcome?

653
00:31:10,140 --> 00:31:12,660
 Is your faith in your church's ability to do something?

654
00:31:12,660 --> 00:31:15,540
 Is your faith in your economic outcome?

655
00:31:15,540 --> 00:31:18,380
 Is your faith in the possibility of what it will look like?

656
00:31:18,380 --> 00:31:21,940
 Where's your faith?

657
00:31:21,940 --> 00:31:28,420
 And if you could find your faith and put it, redirect it into the person of Jesus, you

658
00:31:28,420 --> 00:31:33,260
 will be encountering the one who could drive out the fear, who could answer some of your

659
00:31:33,260 --> 00:31:42,420
 deepest questions, and could help you reimagine a life that is full of the promises and the

660
00:31:42,420 --> 00:31:44,940
 purposes of God.

