00:32:44,300 --> 00:32:49,460
 And then the guy just falls to the ground, and he starts to weep and weep, and he said,

686
00:32:49,460 --> 00:32:53,300
 "I didn't know he was real.

687
00:32:53,300 --> 00:32:56,340
 I didn't know he was real.

688
00:32:56,340 --> 00:32:57,340
 I didn't know he was real."

689
00:32:57,340 --> 00:33:00,940
 You just feel the spirit break out across the room.

690
00:33:00,940 --> 00:33:04,660
 "I didn't know he was real.

691
00:33:04,660 --> 00:33:05,660
 He's real."

692
00:33:05,660 --> 00:33:11,540
 And it's the final question of the, the final question.

693
00:33:11,540 --> 00:33:12,540
 It's just love.

694
00:33:12,780 --> 00:33:15,540
 This is like the state of discipleship for the rest of your life.

695
00:33:15,540 --> 00:33:18,060
 You know, it's not like you ever arrive.

696
00:33:18,060 --> 00:33:23,060
 The disciples, in response to this encounter where they've witnessed Jesus, respond to

697
00:33:23,060 --> 00:33:26,900
 them in care, and compassion, and strength, and power.

698
00:33:26,900 --> 00:33:28,420
 He's with them, not against them.

